Our Mission

Our mission at Paws and Claws is to provide a safe, caring, and welcoming environment for pets in need of a new home, with a focus on supporting the adoption of older pets and puppies. We believe that every pet deserves a second chance, and we are committed to offering the highest level of care and support to all of the animals in our adoption program.

We are dedicated to finding loving families for every animal in our care, and to supporting the well-being of both pets and their new owners every step of the way. We offer a range of resources and support services to help ensure a smooth and successful transition to a new home, including training and behavior support, medical care, and ongoing support for pet owners.

At Paws and Claws, we also strive to educate the community about the importance of responsible pet ownership and the benefits of adopting from a shelter or rescue. We believe that by working together, we can make a positive impact on the lives of pets and people in our community, regardless of the age or breed of the pet.
